As @peter-kehl suggested, until there is a "de-RFC" approved (e.g. as there was for [type ascription](https://rust-lang.github.io/rfcs/3307-de-rfc-type-ascription.html)) that cancels [RFC 213](https://rust-lang.github.io/rfcs/0213-defaulted-type-params.html) (and hopefully would document the problems that need to be overcome), it seems as though this tracking issue should remain open.
